    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1551190/extras/558645267493f0c42368fcc3d3716858.poster.avif?t=1769363620\" width=600 height=82 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1551190/extras/558645267493f0c42368fcc3d3716858.webm?t=1769363620\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1551190/extras/558645267493f0c42368fcc3d3716858.mp4?t=1769363620\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >What is it?</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Mad Chess is a game that maintains standard chess rules while adding 19 more unique factions to the game. Factions have the same pawns and king as classic chess, but the 4 other pieces, while having the same movement patterns, trade their reduced range for RPG abilities that break specific chess rules.  </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This makes Mad Chess easy to learn but hard to master. With 190 match-ups instead of 1, chess just got its biggest expansion pack in centuries. Madness? No. Mad Chess. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1551190/extras/39234172bcd5436b5713a28546c16709.poster.avif?t=1769363620\" width=600 height=66 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1551190/extras/39234172bcd5436b5713a28546c16709.webm?t=1769363620\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1551190/extras/39234172bcd5436b5713a28546c16709.mp4?t=1769363620\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Twenty Factions, including:</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > <u>Humans</u>: Use the classic chess army that you all know with long-ranged units.  </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > <u>Mermaids</u>: Bring the ocean with you by covering the chessboard with water.  </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > <u>Angels</u>: Wield the Divine Light which grants protection &amp; situational invincibility.  </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > <u>Dragons</u>: Gain necrotic bonuses upon having your units captured.  </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > <u>Vampires</u>: Consume your own troops to gain momentum &amp; disturb enemy units.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u>Fairies</u>: Protect your archers to capture enemies without moving from afar. </p></li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Key Features:</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u>Adventure</u>: 70+ missions campaign to help Princess Madeline vanquish the Silver Demons. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u>Versus</u>: Play local games against a decent AI opponent (up to 1300 ELO) or another player. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u>Multiplayer</u>: Play public or private games online against other players with custom rules. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><u>Shop</u>: Earn gold by playing to unlock factions and boards. (<strong>no microtransactions</strong>)</p></li></ul>",
